The objective of Accounting is to provide useful information for decision making. Accountants measure, interpret, and communicate information about organizations. They regularly work with and are a part of top management. People who get advice from accountants and who use their work include investors, creditors, company owners and managers, as well as the government. All business majors at KSU take two Accounting courses - Introduction to Financial Accounting and Introduction to Managerial Accounting. After completing these courses, students should have the basic understanding of Accounting necessary to support any business major.
